Cell.Text: [S] Of course. Take what you need.
[S] Of course. Take what you need. | But what's all this about? What are you two doing here?
Hadvar said you could help me out.
S|Hadvar? How do you know him?
[S] Like I said, I'm glad to help in any way I can. Help yourself to whatever you need, within reason.
Hadvar said you could help me out.
<<Shared>> When he shows up here and vouches for you, then I'll see what I can do for you.

Node.Caption: MQ102RiverwoodHelpTopic: Can you help me out?

Cell.Text: Just head north - you can't miss it. | It's the capital of Whiterun Hold, the biggest and best of the nine holds of Skyrim. But don't take my word for it.

[E] Cross the river and then head north. You'll see it, just past the falls. | When you get to Whiterun just keep going up. When you get to the top of the hill, you're at Dragonsreach, the Jarl's palace.

Just follow the road north. When you get to Honningbrew Meadery, turn left and the road will take you to the city gates. | It's not far. We used to go to the market there every month or so, until the roads got so dangerous with the war and all.

Node.Caption: MQ102WhiterunTopicTopic: How do I get to Whiterun from here?

Cell.Text: I'd be glad to help a friend of Hadvar. But you didn't answer my question - how do you know him?

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpA1: He's a friend. He promised you could help.

Cell.Text: Did he, now? That doesn't sound like my nephew at all. I doubt he'd be mixed up with the likes of you.

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpA2: He helped me escape from prison.

Cell.Text: [S] People are rightly stirred up about the damn Thalmor being allowed to roam around arresting people, just for worshipping Talos. | But was it worth tearing Skyrim apart, and maybe destroying the Empire? No, Ulfric will have a lot to answer for in the end. | Nords have always supported the Empire, and the Empire has always been good for Skyrim.
I just hope the war doesn't come to Riverwood. There's enough trouble in the world without those Stormcloaks stirring up more.

Node.Caption: MQ102ACivilWarTopic: What do you think about the war?

Cell.Text: [S] G|If I make it back to Solitude, I'll put in a good word for you with General Tullius. | The Legion could sure use someone like you. Good luck.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarIntroA4: I think I'll make my own way from here.

Cell.Text: I guess that wasn't such a big deal elsewhere in the Empire, but here it's caused a lot of resentment. Native son and all that. | Even I'll admit it hasn't been the Empire's finest hour. But it wasn't like the Emperor had any choice, did he? | If he hadn't signed the peace treaty with the Thalmor, they would have destroyed the Empire - then where would Skyrim be? | That's the part that Ulfric's supporters always conveniently forget about. Unless the Empire stands together, the Thalmor will destroy us all.
Why are the Thalmor allowed to arrest people for worshipping Talos?

It's from that treaty that ended the Great War, remember, when the Emperor was forced by the Thalmor to outlaw Talos worship. | We didn't pay much attention to it when I was a boy - everyone still had their little shrine to Talos. | But then Ulfric and his "Sons of Skyrim" started agitating about it, and sure enough the Emperor had to crack down. | Dragging people off in the middle of the night... one of the main causes of this war, if you ask me.

Node.Caption: MQ102ATalosTopic: Why is the worship of Talos banned?

Cell.Text: [S] Like I said, I'm glad to help in any way I can. | But I need your help. We need your help.

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpForcegreetTopic

Cell.Text: [S] S|<<Shared>> Closest town from here is Riverwood. My uncle's the blacksmith there. I'm sure he'd help you out.
[S] Changed your mind? Come with me. I'm heading to Riverwood. It's just up the road and my uncle Alvor is the blacksmith there.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarIntroNewTopic

Cell.Text: [S] S|I don't blame you for being angry about it. I would be, too, in your shoes. | But it was all a mistake. You weren't supposed to be on that cart with those Stormcloak traitors. | General Tullius already said you'd be pardoned if you helped us. | And the Imperial Legion needs your help, especially now, with that dragon out there somewhere, and Ulfric back on the loose.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarIntroA1: General Tullius ordered my execution. Why would I want to help him?

Cell.Text: [S] S|No. Not yet. After all, a dragon... something out of old tales and legends... no one could have expected that. | But you can bet he'll be trying to figure it out. This could shift the whole balance of the war. | If you want to help stop that dragon, your best bet is to go to Solitude and join up with the Legion.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarIntroA2: You think General Tullius knows where that dragon came from?

Cell.Text: [S] S|<<Shared>> Listen, you should go to Solitude and join up with the Imperial Legion. We could really use someone like you. | And if the rebels have themselves a dragon, General Tullius is the only one who can stop them.
[S] G|Stick close. Damn rebels could be anywhere. Don't worry, though. General Tullius will have them on the run soon enough.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarIntroA3: Sounds good. Let's go.

Cell.Text: Of course! I know, today wasn't the best introduction to the Legion, but I hope you'll give us another chance. | The Legion could really use someone like you, especially now. | And if the rebels have themselves a dragon, General Tullius is the only one who can stop them.
How do I join the Imperial Legion?

General Tullius has his headquarters in Castle Dour, in the city of Solitude, northwest of here. | You'll want to talk to Legate Rikke. She deals with the new recruits. | I'll be sure to put in a good word for you if I get back to Solitude first.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarJoinLegionTopic: You really think I should join the Imperial Legion?

Cell.Text: G|I hope so. The Legion is Skyrim's only hope right now. Come on, we'd better get moving.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarJoinLegionYes: You make a good case. Maybe I will join up.

Cell.Text: G|Sure, I understand. It's not easy to go from being executed by the Legion one day to joining up the next. | But I think you'll see that the Legion is Skyrim's only hope for real peace right now. I know you'll make the right choice in the end.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarJoinLegionNo: I'll have to think about it.

Cell.Text: What? A dragon? In Helgen? | That explains what I saw earlier... flying down the valley from the south... I was hoping I was wrong about what I thought it was...

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpB1: A dragon attacked Helgen and destroyed it. Hadvar and I escaped together.

Cell.Text: Suit yourself. I hate to turn away any friend of Hadvar, but in times like these... you understand if I can't just take your word for it.

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpB2: Never mind.

Node.ToolTip:
000D231E - Custom, in use by kkuhlmann
Last User:kkuhlmann Date:4/30/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: A dragon... here in Skyrim. What's this world coming to? First the war, now dragons... trouble loves company, they say...

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpC1: It was a dragon. Hadvar will tell you the same thing.

Node.ToolTip:
000D231D - Custom, in use by kkuhlmann
Last User:kkuhlmann Date:4/30/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: You're right, I saw it. Didn't want to believe my own eyes, is all.

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpC2: That dragon flew off this way. You must have seen it.

Cell.Text: [S] The Jarl needs to know if there's a dragon on the loose. Riverwood is defenseless... | We need to get word to Jarl Balgruuf in Whiterun to send whatever soldiers he can. If you'll do that for me, I'll be in your debt.

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpD1

Cell.Text: There's something you could do for me. For all of us here.

Node.Caption: MQ102AlvorHelpD0: Is there something else?

Cell.Text: Jarl Balgruuf? He rules Whiterun Hold. A good man, perhaps a bit over-cautious, but these are dangerous times. | So far he's managed to stay out of the war. I'm afraid it can't last, though.

Node.Caption: MQ102AJarlBalgruufTopic: What can you tell me about the Jarl?

Cell.Text: [S] I don't think he likes either Ulfric or Elisif much. Who can blame him? | But I've no doubt he'll prove loyal to the Empire in the end. He's no traitor.

Node.Caption: MQ102AJarlBalgruufA1: Which side in the war does he favor?

Cell.Text: Of course. Skyrim has always been part of the Empire. | That doesn't mean I support everything the Empire's been doing lately, but Nords have never been fair weather friends.

Node.Caption: MQ102AJarlBalgruufA2: You support the Empire, then?
MQ102AJarlBalgruufB2: Who's Elisif?

Cell.Text: Ah, I forget you're new to Skyrim. Jarl Elisif, I should say, although only because she was married to Jarl Torryg when he was murdered. | Ulfric murdered Torygg, you know. Walked right into his palace in Solitude and killed him. Shouted him to death, if you believe the stories. | That's what started this whole war. The Empire couldn't ignore that. Once the jarls start killing each other, we're back to the bad old days.

Node.Caption: MQ102AElisifTopic: Who's Elisif?

Cell.Text: G|<<Shared>> That's where I'm headed. You can come with me if you want.

Node.Caption: MQ102AHadvarIntroA0
